President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Glyn Townsend Davies as Ambassador to the Kingdom of Thailand, Carol Waller Pope as Member of the Federal Labor Relations Authority (FLRA) and Chairman, and Amanda Hesser as Member of the President's Commission on White House Fellowships. Davies, a career member of the Foreign Service, has held various positions at the Department of State and has extensive experience in international affairs. Pope is currently the Chairman of the FLRA and has previously served as a member of the FLRA and the National Council on Federal Labor-Management Relations. Hesser is the CEO of Food52 and has a background in journalism and culinary arts. She co-founded Food52 and has authored several books on cooking.